  "prompt": "Is there any management quota at PCCOE Pune? What are the fees?",
  "response": "PCCOE (Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering) in Pune does have a management quota for admissions, typically for certain programs such as B.Tech. The management quota allows students who may not have qualified through regular entrance exams to secure a seat in the college by paying a higher fee.\n\nAs for the fees, they can vary based on the program and the academic year, so it's best to check the official PCCOE website or contact the college administration directly for the most current fee structure and details regarding the management quota.\n\nKeep in mind that details like fee structure and quota availability can change frequently, so it's essential to get the latest information directly from the college.",
